-- BNP Paribas says to buy DAB Bank from UniCredit
-- By Andrew Callus
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 02:08PM EDT
-- None



PARIS, July 31 (Reuters) - French bank BNP Paribas <BNPP.PA> said on Thursday it had agreed to buy an 81.4 percent stake in DAB Bank AG <DRNG.DE> from UniCredit <CRDI.MI> unit Hypovereinsbank at 4.78 euros a share in a deal that values the whole of DAB at 435 million euros ($582 million).

